    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Forbidding Advertisement Through Child Exploitation Act of 2013 or the FACE Act of 2013 - Prohibits social media service providers from intentionally or knowingly using for a commercial purpose a self-image uploaded by a minor.</p> <p>Defines &quot;social media service&quot; as any online service that allows an individual to upload, store, and manage personal content to share with other individuals.</p> <p>Requires violations to be treated as an unfair or deceptive act or practice under the Federal Trade Commission Act.</p> <p>Sets forth the enforcement authority of the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) and state attorneys general.</p>]]></text>
